['In our #ICLR2021 paper we study a well-established neurobiological network motif from the fruit fly brain and investigate the possibility of reusing its architecture for solving common natural language processing tasks.
Paper: <LINK> <LINK>', 'Our fruit fly network generates binary logical word embeddings - vectors of [0,1] as opposed to continuous vectors like GloVe and word2vec, which is useful from the perspective of memory efficiency and interpretability.', 'We show that not only can the fruit fly network motif achieve performance comparable to existing methods in NLP, but, additionally, it uses only a fraction of the computational resources (shorter training time and smaller memory footprint).', 'Work done by @YuchenLiangRPI
